ABUJA - Unions in Nigeria are campaigning to increase the country s minimum wage. It's currently set at just over R700 a month.Union leaders say this is unacceptable, as food inflation is currently at 19.3 percent.They want the minimum wage increased to around R2,000.Last week, Nigeria's house of representatives passed a bill, calling for a review of the minimum wage every five years.Like South Africa, Nigeria is currently in a recession.eNCA